review_reason: Mathematical obstruction identified: the plan's inner-chain approach cannot prove forward_F because (1) combined witness+F-preservation seed can be inconsistent, (2) F-formula persistence through Zorn-based Lindenbaum is unprovable, (3) inner chain witnesses don't accumulate. A revised plan using a different chain construction strategy is needed.
summary: Identified fundamental mathematical obstruction in implementation plan v002. The inner-chain approach for F/P witness accumulation fails because the combined seed {psi} union FPreservingSeed(M) can be inconsistent (counterexample: psi = G(neg chi) with F(chi) in M), F-formulas don't persist through Zorn-based Lindenbaum extensions, and inner chain witnesses don't accumulate through GContent stepping. Handoff document written with 4 viable alternative approaches.

artifacts.summary: Detailed analysis of the mathematical obstruction with 4 viable alternative approaches for a revised plan

errors.message: Plan v002's inner-chain approach cannot prove forward_F: (1) {psi} union FPreservingSeed(M) can be inconsistent when psi = G(neg chi) with F(chi) in M, (2) F-formula persistence through Zorn-based Lindenbaum is unprovable - Lindenbaum can add G(neg psi) at any step, (3) inner chain witnesses don't accumulate through GContent-based stepping
errors.recommendation: Create implementation plan v003 using one of the alternative approaches: (A) constructive formula-by-formula Lindenbaum with enumeration order control, (B) canonical model + unraveling, (C) dependent choice with priority queue, or (D) two-step splice construction. Approach A or D appears most viable.
